properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 17 at 3:23PM AKST until February 18 at 6:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 4 to 9
inches expected.

* WHERE...Western Kenai Peninsula north of Anchor Point.

* WHEN...From 3 AM to 6 PM AKST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Light snow will continue through the day
today. However, a more intense system will bring the heaviest
period of snow tonight through noon Tuesday.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO 6 PM AKST TUESDAY NORTH OF ANCHOR POINT
